-- S.Korean shares gain more than 1 pct as financials rally; won higher
-- By Joonhee Yu
-- Wed Oct 22, 2014 02:19AM EDT
-- None



SEOUL, Oct 22 (Reuters) - South Korean shares climbed more than 1 percent on Wednesday to its highest close in nearly two weeks, supported by a broad rally in financials after Wall Street posted strong gains.

The Korea Composite Stock Price Index (KOSPI) <.KS11> rose 1.13 percent to close at 1,936.97 points. The South Korean won <KRW=> was firmer on Wednesday, underpinned by foreign buying of local stocks.